A remarkably bad downfall event, one of the only ones that is worse than it's traditional counterpart. A Close comparison is The Ssssserpent (175 [150] gold for a doubt, or do nothing) from traditional. Icky is at least not as bad of a curse, but you get less souls from world of goop. The big difference is that you can't skip on world of goop, you have to take at least 1 icky, which you will probably card remove later. I suppose if you have repulsor on guardian, automaton, or snecko, you can more reasonably keep the icky (or even multiple of them) in your deck with less issue, but it's still not ideal.

It's kind of strange that you have drain and full harvest as options. I can't really understand when you would take them, barring darkstone periapt and du-vu doll. Maybe if you were playing hermit in downfall mode? Even with periapt and doll, three curses is still going to make your deck significantly less consistent. Bronze idol could turn the icky's into 2 energy to draw 2 cards, but that's also not exciting. Omamori of course can block out multiple curses, so that's another possible reason to take drain. I still believe that sap is the correct option (and one your still unhappy with) over 90 percent of the time. Downfall events are still strong enough in general that this doesn't have that much of an impact on my decision making. At the very least, it gives you some souls to help remove the curse, so mostly your just down the opportunity cost of 1 card remove on a strike/defend later, which is still bad. Sometimes you can stretch the souls for extra value as well if there is a shop very close by, or if you have membership card or courier.
